[3]
From: RS Wallis <rsw2@po.cwru.edu>
Date: Mon, 25 Mar 1996 11:44:28 -0500

This is very interesting. There are some small studies suggesting that
Kinyoun staining of buffy coat smears is helpful in rapid diagnosis of
M. avium infection, but I am not aware of this in tuberculosis.
Were any of the subjects treated with corticosteroids in addition to
TB therapy?
